This project addresses an advanced variant of the irregular strip 
packing problem arising from automotive manufacturing, where the 
shapes of certain pieces (adjustable-edge polygon) can be adjusted 
before cutting. Unlike traditional approaches that only optimize 
piece placement, this problem simultaneously optimizes both the 
shapes and placements of pieces to minimize material waste. The 
project includes 40 benchmark instances and several heuristic 
algorithms for this problem.

to run the solver, simply execute the run program and provide two 
integer arguments: FileIndex and AlgIndex. FileIndex, ranging from 
1 to 40, specifies which instance to solve. AlgIndex, ranging from 
1 to 5, selects the algorithm as follows. 

AlgIndex = 1, Beam Search with Same Area Strategy 
AlgIndex = 2, Beam Search with Different Area Strategy 
AlgIndex = 3, Tabu Search 
AlgIndex = 4, Variable Neighborhood Search
AlgIndex = 5, QLearning Enhanced Variable Neighborhood Search
